{"questionId":"3183322","questionHtml":"<p>A boat travels <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo> </mo><mi>km</mi></math> on a bearing of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>315</mn><mo>°</mo></math> and then a further <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo> </mo><mi>km</mi></math> on a bearing of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>045</mn><mo>°</mo></math>.</p>\n<p>Find the bearing on which the boat should travel to return directly to the starting point.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>diagram showing (approximately) correct directions (and order) for the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>315</mn><mo>°</mo></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>045</mn><mo>°</mo></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src=\"__IMG__/8656c792e465b23b5d92f67fe32d396c760fbf1b.png\"></p>\n<p>recognizing right angle triangle&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct expression to find second angle in triangle&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>arctan</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>arctan</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>correct expression to find bearing&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>arctan</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>135</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>360</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>arctan</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>135</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>172</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>171</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>869</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>diagram showing (approximately) correct directions (and order) for the 315° and 045° (these may be shown in reverse as the return journey)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/1dccdc452c5db5ea4170828507bcfaab8d6f97aa.png\"></p>\n<p>finding the lengths marked <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AP</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BP</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CQ</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BQ</mi></math> in the diagram&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AP</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>BP</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mfrac><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6568</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CQ</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>BQ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mfrac><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2426</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> This may be done using a vector approach.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>using&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>°</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>AP</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>CQ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>PB</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>BQ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> or equivalent to find the direction of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AC</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct expression to find bearing&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>180</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>arctan</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>172</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>171</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>869</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>[5 marks]</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3183322","referenceCode":"23M.1.AHL.TZ1.5","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"A boat travels 8 km on a bearing of 315° and then a further 6 km on a bearing of 045°. Find the bearing on which the boat should travel to return directly to the starting point.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"5","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.3—Angles of elevation and depression"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}